 <text>
  <front>
   <head>To Death.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">O THOU most terrible, most dreaded power,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">In whatsoever form thou meetest the eye!</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Whether thou biddest thy sudden arrow fly</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">In the dread silence of the midnight hour;</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Or whether, hovering o'er the lingering wretch</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thy sad cold javelin hangs suspended long,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">While round the couch the weeping kindred throng</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">With hope and fear alternately on stretch;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Oh, say, for me what horrors are prepared?</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Am I now doomed to meet thy fatal arm?</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Or wilt thou first from life steal every charm,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And bear away each good my soul would guard?</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">That thus, deprived of all it loved, my heart</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">From life itself contentedly may part.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
